{"lemma": "سُبْحَةٌ", "slug": "سُبْحَةٌ", "root": "س.ب.ح", "root_slug": "س-ب-ح", "root_link": "/words/roots/س-ب-ح", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n18667"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "prayer beads", "fa": "تسبیح", "ur": "تسبیح", "tr": "tesbih", "id": "tasbih", "bn": "তাসবিহ", "es": "tasbih", "fr": "tasbih", "de": "Tasbih", "ru": "тасбих", "zh": "泰斯比哈"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "misbaha, rosary"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/sub.ħa/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n18667", "headword_ar": "سُبْحَةٌ", "root": "sbH", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Beads"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "strung"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon a string"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thread,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ninety-nine in number, and having a mark after each thirtythree,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with which"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by counting them,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one performs the act termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~asobiyH", "text_ar": "التَّسْبِيح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the repetition of the praises of God,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "generally consisting in repeating the words"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAna A@ll~`ho", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thirtythree times,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHamodu lil~`ho", "text_ar": "الحَمْدُ لِلّٰهْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thirty-three times, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aall~`hu A^akobaro", "text_ar": "اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَرْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thirty-three times, which is done by many persons after the ordinary prayers, as a supererogatory act]: (S, A, Msb, K:) its appellation implies that it is an Arabic word; but Az says that it is post-classical: its pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subaHN", "text_ar": "سُبَحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subuHaAtN", "text_ar": "سُبُحَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also. (Har p. 133.) See 2, last sentence but one. ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Invocation of God;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supplication:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prayer,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whether obligatory"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supererogatory:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supererogatory praise;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S;) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supererogatory prayer;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Mgh, K;) because of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tasobiyHN", "text_ar": "تَسْبِيحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "therein. (Mgh.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN yuSal~iY Als~uboHapa", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ يُصَلِّى السُّبْحَةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", expl. above; see 2, in the latter part of the paragraph. (Msb.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaDaYsuboHatahu", "text_ar": "قَضَىسُبْحَتَهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He performed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "finished, his prayer:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaDayotu suboHatiY", "text_ar": "قَضَيْتُ سُبْحَتِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I performed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "finished, my supererogatory praise"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such prayer."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Sal~aY", "text_ar": "صَلَّى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~uboHapa", "text_ar": "السُّبْحَةَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He performed the supererogatory prayer:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHapa AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "سُبْحَةَ الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the supererogatory prayer of the period termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~uHaY", "text_ar": "الضُّحَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHapu A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "سُبْحَةُ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (IAth, K, TA,) with damm, (TA, [but in my MS. copy of the K written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saboHap", "text_ar": "سَبْحَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and so in the CK,]) means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The greatness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "majesty, of God:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAth, K, TA:) or [the pl.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~ubuHaAtu", "text_ar": "السُّبُحَاتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", occurring in a trad., means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the greatness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "majesty, and the light"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "splendour"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of God:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) or by the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subuHaAtu wajohi", "text_ar": "سُبُحَاتُ وَجْهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~inaA", "text_ar": "رَبِّنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with damm to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "b", "text_ar": "ب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", is meant (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the greatness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "majesty, of the face of our Lord:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subuHaAtu wajohi A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "سُبُحَاتُ وَجْهِ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the lights"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "splendours"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (K,) or, accord. to ISh,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the light"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "splendour"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the face of God:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(ISh, K, TA:) some say that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "subuHaAtu Alwajohi", "text_ar": "سُبُحَاتُ الوَجْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the beauties of the face;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because, when you see a person of beautiful face, you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAna A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[to express your admiration]: and some, that [when it relates to God] it denotes a declaration of his being far removed from every imperfection; meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAna wajohihi", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانَ وَجْهِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA. [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAn", "text_ar": "سُبْحَان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) One says, [addressing God,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asoA^aluka bisubuHaAti wajohika", "text_ar": "اَسْاَلُكَ بِسُبُحَاتِ وَجْهِكَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alkariymi", "text_ar": "الكَرِيمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with two dammehs, meaning (tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I ask Thee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by the evidences of thy greatness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "majesty,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the greatness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "majesty, of thy glorious face,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by the acknowledgement whereof thy praise is celebrated."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~ubuHaAtu", "text_ar": "السُّبُحَاتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The places of prostration"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[probably meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the reciting of the Kur-án"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K.)       -A2-  Also, i. e. [the sing.,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHapN", "text_ar": "سُبْحَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A piece of cotton."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "K", "TA", "A", "IAth", "ISh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}